commit.message: Don't make build depend on flake8

Drop setup.py, use just a Makefile and a private package

We've had this half-Makefile and half-setup.py solution for a while now,
but still I'm tired of the fragmentation and immaturity that remains in
the Python packaging ecosystem and also differences in how distros
handle installation paths of packages. Going full Makefile should
hopefully liberate me (and users?) from these troubles.

I don't think there was ever even any proper reason for installing a
package in the regular Python dist-packages search path. It's just how
I, without knowing much, thought it should be done.

Add missing PREFIX to build step

Hasn't caused any issue if using PREFIX=/usr/local, since that's the default in
the Makefile too.
Use Cascadia Mono instead of Code to avoid ligatures
Work around a segfault closing preferences dialog

Add missing filesystem permission to Flatpak

How did this work before?
